==Malayalam==
===Noun===
'''അച്ഛന് ''' (atʃtʃhan)
#[[father]]
====Declension====

=====Singular=====

* '''Nominative''': അച്ഛന് ..........    ''/atʃtʃhan/'' 
* '''Vocative''': അച്ഛാ    ..........    ''/atʃtʃhaː/''
* '''Accusative''': അച്ഛനെ  ..........  ''/atʃtʃhane/'' 
* '''Dative''': അച്ഛന്    ..........     ''/atʃtʃhan(u)/'' 
* '''Genitive''': അച്ഛന്റ്റെ   ..........  ''/atʃtʃhante/''
* '''Locative''': അച്ഛനില്   ..........   ''/atʃtʃhanil2/''

=====Plural=====
* '''Nominative''': അച്ഛന്മാര്  ..........      ''/atʃtʃhanmaːr/'' 
* '''Vocative''': അച്ഛന്മാരേ   ..........      ''/atʃtʃhanmaːreː/'' 
* '''Accusative''': അച്ഛന്മാരെ  ..........     ''/atʃtʃhanmaːre/'' 
* '''Dative''': അച്ഛന്മാര്ക്ക്     ..........      ''/atʃtʃhanmaːrkk(u)/'' 
* '''Genitive''': അച്ഛന്മാരുടെ ..........       ''/atʃtʃhanmaːruʈe/'' 
* '''Locative''': അച്ഛന്മാരില് ..........        ''/atʃtʃhanmaːril/''

====Synonyms====

* പിതാവ്   ..........  ''/piθaːʋ(u/)'' ..........   This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitar'' and is considered very formal.
* തന്ത    ..........   ''/θaɳθa/'' ..........     This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
* ബാപ്പ  ..........      ''/baːppa/''  ..........      This is the word that most Muslims who speak malayalam use for father.
* അപ്പന്  ..........''/appan/''.......... or അപ്പച്ഛന് .......... ''/appatʃtʃhan/''.......... These are usually used by Christians who use അച്ഛന് to refer to priests (with irregular vocative അച്ഛോ (''/atʃtʃhoː/'')  most of the time).

